<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,151,644]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,188,212]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ruppel" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[323,514,188,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platipes">
<emphasis box="[323,514,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Micippa platipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is always confused with its close congener 
<taxonomicName authority="(Herbst, 1803)" baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[1017,1313,188,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philyra">
<emphasis box="[1017,1040,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1056,1137,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
(Herbst, 1803)
</taxonomicName>
. The latter has been frequently recorded from the Persian Gulf [
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[745,914,223,247]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="13 - 159" refId="ref51383" refString="Nobili, G. (1906 a) Crustaces decapodes et stomatopodes. In: Mission J. Bonnier et Ch. Perez (Golfe Persique, 1901). Bulletin Scientifique de la France et de la Belgique, 40, 13 - 159, pls. 2 - 7." type="journal article" year="1906">Nobili (1906a)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kossmann" authorityYear="1877" box="[953,1271,224,248]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="philyra" variety="mascarenica">
<emphasis box="[953,976,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[991,1072,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1129,1271,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">mascarenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Arzanah I.; 
<bibRefCitation author="Stephensen, K." box="[184,395,260,284]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="57 - 237" refId="ref52943" refString="Stephensen, K. (1946) The Brachyura of the Iranian Gulf. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part IV. E. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 57 - 237." type="book chapter" year="1946">Stephensen (1946)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kossmann" authorityYear="1877" box="[437,759,260,284]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="philyra" variety="mascarenica">
<emphasis box="[437,460,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[476,557,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[617,759,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">mascarenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[832,924,260,284]" name="Bahrain" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Bahrain</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, G. &amp; Murray, J. W. &amp; Biggs, H. E. J. &amp; Bate, R. &amp; Bush P. R." box="[938,1157,260,284]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="233 - 277" refId="ref46962" refString="Evans, G., Murray, J. W., Biggs, H. E. J., Bate, R. &amp; Bush P. R. (1973) The oceanography, ecology, sedimentology and geomorphology of parts of the Trucial Coast Barrier Island Complex, Persian Gulf. In: Purser, B. H. (ed.): The Persian Gulf. - Holocene carbonate sedimentation and diagenesis in a shallow epicontinental sea. Springer Verlag, Berlin, 233 - 277." type="book chapter" year="1973">
Evans 
<emphasis box="[1015,1065,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (1973)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Titgen, R. H." box="[1216,1372,260,284]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref53402" refString="Titgen, R. H. (1982) The systematics and ecology of the Decapods of Dubai, and their zoogeographic relationships to the Persian Gulf and the Western Indian Ocean. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Texas A &amp; M University, 292 pp." type="book" year="1982">Titgen (1982)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,212,295,319]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">UAE</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Basson, P. W. &amp; Burchard, J. E. &amp; Hardy, J. T. &amp; Price, A. R. G." box="[224,451,295,320]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref45702" refString="Basson, P. W., Burchard, J. E., Hardy, J. T. &amp; Price, A. R. G. (1977) Biotopes of the Western Arabian Gulf: Marine life and environments of Saudi Arabia. ARAMCO, Dept. of Loss Prevention and environmental affairs, Dhahran: 289 pp." type="book" year="1977">
Basson 
<emphasis box="[312,362,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (1977)
</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[521,673,295,319]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M." box="[684,821,295,319]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel (2001)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[891,1038,295,319]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1094,1158,295,319]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">UAE</collectingCountry>
]. 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M." box="[1176,1313,295,319]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel (2001)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the Persian Gulf records all could be clearly assigned to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[779,897,332,356]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philyra">
<emphasis box="[779,802,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[816,897,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Buitendijk (1939) prepared detailed remarks in order to distinguish these two similar species, and provided synonymies for both species using literature records. By using Buitendijk (1939) and the key provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Griffin, D. J. G. &amp; Tranter, H. A." box="[775,1062,404,428]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 335" refId="ref47564" refString="Griffin, D. J. G. &amp; Tranter, H. A. (1986) The Decapoda Brachyura of the Siboga Expedition. Part VIII. Majidae. Siboga Expeditie Monographie, 39 c 4, 1 - 335." type="journal article" year="1986">Griffin &amp; Tranter (1986)</bibRefCitation>
the present specimens from the Iranian coast of the Persian Gulf could be convincingly identified as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ruppel" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[927,1053,440,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platipes">
<emphasis box="[927,950,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[964,1053,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">platipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We could not examine the single male of 
<bibRefCitation author="Stephensen, K." box="[242,451,476,500]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="57 - 237" refId="ref52943" refString="Stephensen, K. (1946) The Brachyura of the Iranian Gulf. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part IV. E. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 57 - 237." type="book chapter" year="1946">Stephensen (1946)</bibRefCitation>
collected by Danish Expedition from 
<collectingCountry box="[878,969,476,500]" name="Bahrain" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Bahrain</collectingCountry>
, but the drawing of the male G1 provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stephensen, K." box="[185,442,511,535]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="57 - 237" refId="ref52943" refString="Stephensen, K. (1946) The Brachyura of the Iranian Gulf. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part IV. E. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 57 - 237." type="book chapter" year="1946">Stephensen (1946: 109</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 21e–f) is very similar to the figure of the G1 provided by Buitendijk (1939: 253, fig. 22) for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ruppel" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[248,381,548,572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platipes">
<emphasis box="[248,271,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[292,381,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">platipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[626,751,548,572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philyra">
<emphasis box="[626,649,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[670,751,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although, 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M." box="[898,1040,548,572]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel (2001)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the Persian Gulf specimens, which are all recorded from the Arabian coast, are 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[860,979,584,608]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philyra">
<emphasis box="[860,883,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[898,979,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We think that still all the material must be re-examined in order to clarify the occurrence of these two species in the Persian Gulf.
</paragraph>
